OL,7,FGwyneth is firm in her assertion that
OL,8,Fthose who are non-verbal can be
OL,9,Fprejudiced against when it comes to
OL,10,Fhospital treatment. She gives me a
OL,11,Fstark example.
OL,13,FOver twenty years ago, when Jeffrey
OL,14,Fwas living in an assisted living
OL,15,Ffacility, he fell in the bath and
OL,16,Frequired hospitalisation.
OL,18,FHe needed an operation to repair his
OL,19,Fdamaged kneecap.
OL,1,W~k4 jw=hw1 hw}h7}j7}            G3/13
