OL,3,CFamilies tell Up Close that system is
OL,4,C'stacked against' those with
OL,5,Cdisabilities
OL,7,FAn issue she says her other able
OL,8,Fbodied children wouldn't face.
OL,10,FShe says: "If we took them in aged 6
OL,11,Fand we said this child has changed
OL,12,Fdrastically or we said he's falling
OL,13,Fover, he's losing balance he's having
OL,14,Fabsence periods I feel they'd be
OL,15,Finvestigated straight away. They'd be
OL,16,Foffered all the tests, whereas we have
OL,17,Fjust been told his issues are a
OL,18,Fcombination of his three diagnoses."
OL,1,W~k4 jw=hw1 hw}h7}j7}            G7/13
