OL,7,FIn a statement, the Department of
OL,8,FHealth said: "The Department is aware
OL,9,Fthat that people with learning
OL,10,Fdisabilities can face barriers in
OL,11,Faccessing general healthcare services,
OL,12,Fincluding GPs and hospitals.
OL,14,F"It is critical that such services are
OL,15,Freasonably adjusted to enable equity
OL,16,Fof access and equity of outcome. Such
OL,17,Fadjustments should also include
OL,18,Fspecialist supports, such as annual
OL,19,Fhealth checks, health facilitation,
OL,20,Fhealth passports and hospital liaison
OL,21,Fservices.
OL,1,W~k4 jw=hw1 hw}h7}j7}           G12/13
